  "prompt": "What are the abbreviations for degrees?",
  "response": "There are numerous abbreviations for academic degrees, some of which are listed below:\n\n1. Associate Degree:\n   - A.A. or A.A.S. (Associate of Arts or Associate of Applied Science)\n   - A.S. (Associate of Science)\n\n2. Bachelor's Degree:\n   - B.A. or A.B. (Bachelor of Arts)\n   - B.S. or S.B. (Bachelor of Science)\n   - B.B.A. (Bachelor of Business Administration)\n   - B.F.A. (Bachelor of Fine Arts)\n\n3. Master's Degree:\n   - M.A. (Master of Arts)\n   - M.S. (Master of Science)\n   - M.B.A. (Master of Business Administration)\n   - M.F.A. (Master of Fine Arts)\n   - M.Ed. (Master of Education)\n\n4. Doctoral Degree:\n   - Ph.D. or D.Phil. (Doctor of Philosophy)\n   - Ed.D. (Doctor of Education)\n   - D.B.A. (Doctor of Business Administration)\n   - M.D. (Doctor of Medicine)\n   - J.D. (Juris Doctor, Doctor of Law)\n\nPlease note that this list is not exhaustive, and there are many other degree abbreviations depending on the field of study and the country's educational system.",
